
    How pagination is calculated - steps:

    1. Calculate number of pages available

    This step is done on the backend side (not by the react app)
    totalNumberOfMovies / moviesPerPage âŸ¹ Math.ceil(numbersOfPagesAvailable);
    Example: 100 movies / 5 movies per page âŸ¹ 20 pages available (total page number)
    Types: number / number = number

    2. Store all page numbers available in a new array

    The data type needs to be changed, from a number (integer) to an array of integers
    const pageNumbersAvailable = _.range(first index, last index);
    Example: 50 (integer) is converted to: [1, 2, 3, ... , 50] (array of integers)

    3. Map over the array of numbers created

    Each individual page number can now be rendered to the screen
    [1, 2, 3, 4].map( pageNumber => (
     <ul>
       <li>
         <a>{pageNumber}</a>
         </li>
    </ul>
    ));